				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Trial of Flame ?<a name="28449"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 04 4:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey guys, I'm seeing if anyone has knowledge on the trial of flame in the PoJ.  I know that it is soloable for a bard and have soloed it several times now but I'm still having some trouble.  I'm trying to farm some pp for my 65 spells, namely our 65 mez but have run into some difficulties with the trial.
<br />

<br />
It's my understanding that the Fiery Aggressor is more difficult than the Burning Nemesis but I find it the other way around.  For me it's easier to mez a flame guy  oos him and drag him away from the others and then stick him on fiery aggressor and then I chant the aggressor down while pet attacks, my pet breaks charm fiarly often but I'm usually able to recharm him and eventually get the aggressor down.
<br />

<br />
The Burning Nemesis on the other hand is giving me more problems.  He doesn't stay for as long a period of time away from the pole as the Fiery Aggressor, so I don't have time to mez a flame guy oos him then charm him to send him in.  The best tactic I've found for this guy is to turn walk on and this with run 3 allows me to stay out of melee range with him still chasing me.  The problem is that after getting him down to 30% he stops to cast a spell on me  and gets out of melee range and then goes back to the pole.  This is frustrating because I spend 5 minutes chanting him down and then have to start over.  The one time I succeeded in taking the Burning Nemesis down I had about 10% health left and I did that on purpose because he was still chasing me, so I thought that low health aggro might have kept him on me, or maybe it was just a coincidence.  But anyway, the score is around Burning Nemesis 4 and Beula 1.
<br />

<br />
Any tips or suggestions would be helpful, I'm a 65 bard with most spells up to 65 and have around 28 AAs.  I see the possiblity of farming pp here but so far haven't been able to get this trivialized yet.  Any help would be appreciated.
<br />

<br />
-B.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
