				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Trial of Flame ?<a name="28457"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 04 5:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You got the set to walk part right but you have to kite running backwards. You will still be slightly faster (with run3)than them and you can watch when they start to run for the pole. Dont bother with charming anything just pull named when he starts to buff up and stay on the wall when you kite, you can regulate your speed by rubbing on the wall. The rest of my strategy is twist PoV and 3 DoTs, toggle yourself and mob so you can quickly target yourself to cancel magic or cure poison/disease to remove DoTs. PoV is needed because of the variety of spells the names use. I also use wind of marr and the seemingly forgotten Niv's melody of preservation as the the two regens stack and get you healed quick. Btw maybe its just me but since GoD came out the named mobs seem to spawn a lot less, I used to let Helms and Mask of the Witness rot I had so many. Now I would like the helms again because the tribute master gives 1200 points for them, never checked points on the mask.</span></td>
