				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Trial of Flame ?<a name="34669"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 14 04 1:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The trial of the executioner is the one for the flag.  The trial of flame is soloable by bards, but not to complete the trial, just for loot.  So what I do, and I assume most other bards that solo this is start the trial.  After 30 seconds to a minute 4 mobs spawn and path to the center pole.  They won't agro you unless you attack.  2 names have a chance of spawning, A Burning Nemesis and a Fiery Aggressor.  These are your loot bags and why you are there.  So if one is up I chant kite it around, and if one doesn't spawn during the first round I just leave the trial and try again.  So no, I've never soloed the entire trial, but I have made some nice pp spending time doing the trial.
<br />

<br />
Also, I'm not the most knowledgable bard out there, and I'm not entirely sure how all the trials go, but the trial you are talking about sounds like the Trial of Execution, the one for the PoV/PoS flag and an AA.  If that is the case it is an entirely different Trial than the Trial of Flame. </span></td>
